title: The Blue Jays play game one of the ALDS
text: Fans cheer as the national anthems are sung to kick off game one of the American League Division Series between the Toronto Blue Jays and the Texas Rangers Oct 8, 2015 in Toronto.(John Lehmann/The Globe and Mail) Toronto Blue Jays players line up for the opening ceremonies of game one of the American League Division Series against the Texas Rangers Oct 8, 2015 in Toronto.(John Lehmann/The Globe and Mail) Fans cheer as the national anthems are sung to kick off game one of the American League Division Series between the Toronto Blue Jays and the Texas Rangers Oct 8, 2015 in Toronto.(John Lehmann/The Globe and Mail) Toronto Blue Jays starting pitcher David Price throws a first inning pitch against the Texas Rangers in game one of the American League Division Series Oct 8, 2015 in Toronto.(John Lehmann/The Globe and Mail) Toronto Blue Jays starting pitcher David Price throws a first inning pitch against the Texas Rangers in game one of the American League Division Series Oct 8, 2015 in Toronto.(Mark Blinch for The Globe and Mail) Texas Rangers' Delino DeShields slides safe into home plate past Toronto Blue Jays' catcher Russell Martin during third inning of game one American League Division Series play Oct 8, 2015 in Toronto.(John Lehmann/The Globe and Mail) Toronto Blue Jays starting pitcher David Price throws a first inning pitch against the Texas Rangers in game one of the American League Division Series Oct 8, 2015 in Toronto.(Fred Lum/The Globe and Mail) See more galleries
